  "texts": [
    "This defines a reversible path in the system's Hamiltonian 𝐻(𝜆), connecting the initial (𝜆 = 0) and final (𝜆 = 1) equilibrium states.",
    "The corresponding free energy change is given by the standard thermodynamic integration expression 93:",
    "Where 𝜕𝐻 𝜕𝜆 ⁄ is the force 𝐹(𝑧) exerted by the wall on the fluid scaled by (𝑧 𝑓𝑖𝑛𝑎𝑙 -𝑧 𝑖𝑛𝑖𝑡𝑖𝑎𝑙).",
    "Changing variables from 𝜆 to z and dividing by the interfacial area 𝐴, one obtains work of adhesion:",
    "which we compute numerically from the discrete data shown in Figure 2."
